Overpass
Overpass piqued me interest as a potential everyday tool of some use. I’m going to try and learn it.
Lets start easy, everything in the box:
nwr({{bbox}});
out meta;
(nwr means ‘node or way or relation’)
Now lets just find a coord:
[out:json];
way[highway](around:50.0,{point.lat},{point.lon});
out;
Pubs in Insch: note, the original search for Insch is overwritten by the search for pubs relative to it.
nwr[name="Insch"]({{bbox}});
nwr[amenity=pub](around:1000);
out center;
Pubs relative to a starting coordinate:
node(around:50,57.3433947,-2.6120391);
nwr[amenity=pub](around:2000);
(._;&gt;;);
out meta;
All amenities or shops near Insch:
node(around:50,57.3433947,-2.6120391);
(
  nwr[amenity](around:2000);
  nwr[shop](around:2000);
);
(._;&gt;;);
out meta;
